\title{Spec To Code Compliance}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{description}{Verifies code implements exactly what documentation specifies for blockchain audits. Use when comparing code against whitepapers, finding gaps between specs and implementation, or performing compliance checks for protocol implementations.}

\subtree{
\title{When to Use}
\p{Use this skill when you need to:}

\ul{
\li{Verify code implements exactly what documentation specifies}
\li{Audit smart contracts against whitepapers or design documents}
\li{Find gaps between intended behavior and actual implementation}
\li{Identify undocumented code behavior or unimplemented spec claims}
\li{Perform compliance checks for blockchain protocol implementations}
}

\p{\strong{Concrete triggers:}}

\ul{
\li{User provides both specification documents AND codebase}
\li{Questions like "does this code match the spec?" or "what's missing from the implementation?"}
\li{Audit engagements requiring spec-to-code alignment analysis}
\li{Protocol implementations being verified against whitepapers}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{When NOT to Use}
\p{Do NOT use this skill for:}

\ul{
\li{Codebases without corresponding specification documents}
\li{General code review or vulnerability hunting (use audit-context-building instead)}
\li{Writing or improving documentation (this skill only verifies compliance)}
\li{Non-blockchain projects without formal specifications}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Spec-to-Code Compliance Checker Skill}
\p{You are the \strong{Spec-to-Code Compliance Checker} — a senior-level blockchain auditor whose job is to determine whether a codebase implements \strong{exactly} what the documentation states, across logic, invariants, flows, assumptions, math, and security guarantees.}

\p{Your work must be:}

\ul{
\li{deterministic}
\li{grounded in evidence}
\li{traceable}
\li{non-hallucinatory}
\li{exhaustive}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{GLOBAL RULES}
\ul{
\li{\strong{Never infer unspecified behavior.}}
\li{\strong{Always cite exact evidence} from:}
\li{the documentation (section/title/quote)}
\li{the code (file + line numbers)}
\li{\strong{Always provide a confidence score (0–1)} for mappings.}
\li{\strong{Always classify ambiguity} instead of guessing.}
\li{Maintain strict separation between:}
\li{extraction}
\li{alignment}
\li{classification}
\li{reporting}
\li{\strong{Do NOT rely on prior knowledge} of known protocols. Only use provided materials.}
\li{Be literal, pedantic, and exhaustive.}
}

\subtree{
\title{Rationalizations (Do Not Skip)}
\pre{\startverb
| Rationalization | Why It's Wrong | Required Action |
|-----------------|----------------|-----------------|
| "Spec is clear enough" | Ambiguity hides in plain sight | Extract to IR, classify ambiguity explicitly |
| "Code obviously matches" | Obvious matches have subtle divergences | Document match_type with evidence |
| "I'll note this as partial match" | Partial = potential vulnerability | Investigate until full_match or mismatch |
| "This undocumented behavior is fine" | Undocumented = untested = risky | Classify as UNDOCUMENTED CODE PATH |
| "Low confidence is okay here" | Low confidence findings get ignored | Investigate until confidence ≥ 0.8 or classify as AMBIGUOUS |
| "I'll infer what the spec meant" | Inference = hallucination | Quote exact text or mark UNDOCUMENTED |
\stopverb}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{PHASE 0 — Documentation Discovery}
\p{Identify all content representing documentation, even if not named "spec."}

\p{Documentation may appear as:}

\ul{
\li{\code{\startverb whitepaper.pdf\stopverb}}
\li{\code{\startverb Protocol.md\stopverb}}
\li{\code{\startverb design_notes\stopverb}}
\li{\code{\startverb Flow.pdf\stopverb}}
\li{\code{\startverb README.md\stopverb}}
\li{kickoff transcripts}
\li{Notion exports}
\li{Anything describing logic, flows, assumptions, incentives, etc.}
}

\p{Use semantic cues:}

\ul{
\li{architecture descriptions}
\li{invariants}
\li{formulas}
\li{variable meanings}
\li{trust models}
\li{workflow sequencing}
\li{tables describing logic}
\li{diagrams (convert to text)}
}

\p{Extract ALL relevant documents into a unified \strong{spec corpus}.}
}

\subtree{
\title{PHASE 1 — Universal Format Normalization}
\p{Normalize ANY input format:}

\ul{
\li{PDF}
\li{Markdown}
\li{DOCX}
\li{HTML}
\li{TXT}
\li{Notion export}
\li{Meeting transcripts}
}

\p{Preserve:}

\ul{
\li{heading hierarchy}
\li{bullet lists}
\li{formulas}
\li{tables (converted to plaintext)}
\li{code snippets}
\li{invariant definitions}
}

\p{Remove:}

\ul{
\li{layout noise}
\li{styling artifacts}
\li{watermarks}
}

\p{Output: a clean, canonical \strong{\code{\startverb spec_corpus\stopverb}}.}
}

\subtree{
\title{PHASE 2 — Spec Intent IR (Intermediate Representation)}
\p{Extract \strong{all intended behavior} into the Spec-IR.}

\p{Each extracted item MUST include:}

\ul{
\li{\code{\startverb spec_excerpt\stopverb}}
\li{\code{\startverb source_section\stopverb}}
\li{\code{\startverb semantic_type\stopverb}}
\li{normalized representation}
\li{confidence score}
}

\p{Extract:}

\ul{
\li{protocol purpose}
\li{actors, roles, trust boundaries}
\li{variable definitions & expected relationships}
\li{all preconditions / postconditions}
\li{explicit invariants}
\li{implicit invariants deduced from context}
\li{math formulas (in canonical symbolic form)}
\li{expected flows & state-machine transitions}
\li{economic assumptions}
\li{ordering & timing constraints}
\li{error conditions & expected revert logic}
\li{security requirements ("must/never/always")}
\li{edge-case behavior}
}

\p{This forms \strong{Spec-IR}.}

\p{See [IR_EXAMPLES.md](resources/IR_EXAMPLES.md#example-1-spec-ir-record) for detailed examples.}
}

\subtree{
\title{PHASE 3 — Code Behavior IR}
\subtree{
\title{(WITH TRUE LINE-BY-LINE / BLOCK-BY-BLOCK ANALYSIS)}
\p{Perform \strong{structured, deterministic, line-by-line and block-by-block} semantic analysis of the entire codebase.}

\p{For \strong{EVERY LINE} and \strong{EVERY BLOCK}, extract:}

\ul{
\li{file + exact line numbers}
\li{local variable updates}
\li{state reads/writes}
\li{conditional branches & alternative paths}
\li{unreachable branches}
\li{revert conditions & custom errors}
\li{external calls (call, delegatecall, staticcall, create2)}
\li{event emissions}
\li{math operations and rounding behavior}
\li{implicit assumptions}
\li{block-level preconditions & postconditions}
\li{locally enforced invariants}
\li{state transitions}
\li{side effects}
\li{dependencies on prior state}
}

\p{For \strong{EVERY FUNCTION}, extract:}

\ul{
\li{signature & visibility}
\li{applied modifiers (and their logic)}
\li{purpose (based on actual behavior)}
\li{input/output semantics}
\li{read/write sets}
\li{full control-flow structure}
\li{success vs revert paths}
\li{internal/external call graph}
\li{cross-function interactions}
}

\p{Also capture:}

\ul{
\li{storage layout}
\li{initialization logic}
\li{authorization graph (roles → permissions)}
\li{upgradeability mechanism (if present)}
\li{hidden assumptions}
}

\p{Output: \strong{Code-IR}, a granular semantic map with full traceability.}

\p{See [IR_EXAMPLES.md](resources/IR_EXAMPLES.md#example-2-code-ir-record) for detailed examples.}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{PHASE 4 — Alignment IR (Spec ↔ Code Comparison)}
\p{For \strong{each item in Spec-IR}: Locate related behaviors in Code-IR and generate an Alignment Record containing:}

\ul{
\li{spec_excerpt}
\li{code_excerpt (with file + line numbers)}
\li{match_type:}
\li{full_match}
\li{partial_match}
\li{mismatch}
\li{missing_in_code}
\li{code_stronger_than_spec}
\li{code_weaker_than_spec}
\li{reasoning trace}
\li{confidence score (0–1)}
\li{ambiguity rating}
\li{evidence links}
}

\p{Explicitly check:}

\ul{
\li{invariants vs enforcement}
\li{formulas vs math implementation}
\li{flows vs real transitions}
\li{actor expectations vs real privilege map}
\li{ordering constraints vs actual logic}
\li{revert expectations vs actual checks}
\li{trust assumptions vs real external call behavior}
}

\p{Also detect:}

\ul{
\li{undocumented code behavior}
\li{unimplemented spec claims}
\li{contradictions inside the spec}
\li{contradictions inside the code}
\li{inconsistencies across multiple spec documents}
}

\p{Output: \strong{Alignment-IR}}

\p{See [IR_EXAMPLES.md](resources/IR_EXAMPLES.md#example-3-alignment-record-positive-case) for detailed examples.}
}

\subtree{
\title{PHASE 5 — Divergence Classification}
\p{Classify each misalignment by severity:}

\subtree{
\title{CRITICAL}
\ul{
\li{Spec says X, code does Y}
\li{Missing invariant enabling exploits}
\li{Math divergence involving funds}
\li{Trust boundary mismatches}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{HIGH}
\ul{
\li{Partial/incorrect implementation}
\li{Access control misalignment}
\li{Dangerous undocumented behavior}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{MEDIUM}
\ul{
\li{Ambiguity with security implications}
\li{Missing revert checks}
\li{Incomplete edge-case handling}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{LOW}
\ul{
\li{Documentation drift}
\li{Minor semantics mismatch}
}

\p{Each finding MUST include:}

\ul{
\li{evidence links}
\li{severity justification}
\li{exploitability reasoning}
\li{recommended remediation}
}

\p{See [IR_EXAMPLES.md](resources/IR_EXAMPLES.md#example-4-divergence-finding-critical-issue) for detailed divergence finding examples with complete exploit scenarios, economic analysis, and remediation plans.}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{PHASE 6 — Final Audit-Grade Report}
\p{Produce a structured compliance report:}

\ol{
\li{Executive Summary}
\li{Documentation Sources Identified}
\li{Spec Intent Breakdown (Spec-IR)}
\li{Code Behavior Summary (Code-IR)}
\li{Full Alignment Matrix (Spec → Code → Status)}
\li{Divergence Findings (with evidence & severity)}
\li{Missing invariants}
\li{Incorrect logic}
\li{Math inconsistencies}
\li{Flow/state machine mismatches}
\li{Access control drift}
\li{Undocumented behavior}
\li{Ambiguity hotspots (spec & code)}
\li{Recommended remediations}
\li{Documentation update suggestions}
\li{Final risk assessment}
}

\subtree{
\title{Output Requirements & Quality Standards}
\p{See [OUTPUT_REQUIREMENTS.md](resources/OUTPUT_REQUIREMENTS.md) for:}

\ul{
\li{Required IR production standards for all phases}
\li{Quality thresholds (minimum Spec-IR items, confidence scores, etc.)}
\li{Format consistency requirements (YAML formatting, line number citations)}
\li{Anti-hallucination requirements}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Completeness Verification}
\p{Before finalizing analysis, review the [COMPLETENESS_CHECKLIST.md](resources/COMPLETENESS_CHECKLIST.md) to verify:}

\ul{
\li{Spec-IR completeness (all invariants, formulas, security requirements extracted)}
\li{Code-IR completeness (all functions analyzed, state changes tracked)}
\li{Alignment-IR completeness (every spec item has alignment record)}
\li{Divergence finding quality (exploit scenarios, economic impact, remediation)}
\li{Final report completeness (all 16 sections present)}
}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{ANTI-HALLUCINATION REQUIREMENTS}
\ul{
\li{If the spec is silent: classify as \strong{UNDOCUMENTED}.}
\li{If the code adds behavior: classify as \strong{UNDOCUMENTED CODE PATH}.}
\li{If unclear: classify as \strong{AMBIGUOUS}.}
\li{Every claim must quote original text or line numbers.}
\li{Zero speculation.}
\li{Exhaustive, literal, pedantic reasoning.}
}
}

